parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Pan and Oil Leveler Monitor Switch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pan and oil leveler monitor switch can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause engine stalling, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

The failure of the ABS system can lead to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially on wet pavement.
